# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 📝 CONFIGURATION NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 🔒 SECURITY BEST PRACTICES:
#
# 1. Always use HTTPS URLs (never git:// or ssh://)
# 2. Set shallow = true for faster clones (except critical modules)
# 3. Pin specific branches for stability
# 4. Use 'update = rebase' to avoid merge conflicts
# 5. Regularly update submodules: git submodule update --remote --merge
# 6. Verify submodule integrity after updates
# 7. Never commit sensitive data in submodules
# 8. Review submodule changes before merging
#
# 🔧 MANAGEMENT COMMANDS:
#
# Initialize all submodules:
#   git submodule update --init --recursive
#
# Update all submodules to latest:
#   git submodule update --remote --merge
#
# Update specific submodule:
#   git submodule update --remote modules/security/trivy
#
# Check submodule status:
#   git submodule status
#
# Remove submodule:
#   git submodule deinit -f modules/path/to/module
#   git rm -f modules/path/to/module
#   rm -rf .git/modules/modules/path/to/module
#
# 📊 STATISTICS:
# Total Submodules: 30+
# Security Tools: 15+
# Threat Intel: 3+
# Container Security: 3+
# Network Security: 3+
